# External Integrations

## Linear Integration

### Setup
- OAuth or API key auth
- Settings page for Linear team/project selection

### Features
- Creates issues with title, description, labels
- Attaches media (screenshot/video)
- Links back to FeedbackFlow ticket
- Optional: syncs status back

### Usage

```typescript
// lib/integrations/linear.ts
import { LinearClient } from "@linear/sdk";

export async function exportToLinear(
  feedback: Feedback,
  ticketDraft: TicketDraft,
  integration: Integration
) {
  const client = new LinearClient({ apiKey: integration.accessToken });
  
  const issue = await client.createIssue({
    teamId: integration.settings.linearTeamId,
    title: ticketDraft.title,
    description: ticketDraft.description,
    labelIds: integration.settings.linearLabelIds,
  });
  
  return {
    externalId: issue.id,
    externalUrl: issue.url,
  };
}
```

## Notion Integration

### Setup
- OAuth connection
- User shares specific database with integration

### Features
- Creates pages in selected database
- Maps properties (title, status, priority)
- Embeds screenshots in page
- Links video if applicable

### Usage

```typescript
// lib/integrations/notion.ts
import { Client } from "@notionhq/client";

export async function exportToNotion(
  feedback: Feedback,
  ticketDraft: TicketDraft,
  integration: Integration
) {
  const notion = new Client({ auth: integration.accessToken });
  
  const page = await notion.pages.create({
    parent: { database_id: integration.settings.notionDatabaseId },
    properties: {
      Title: { title: [{ text: { content: ticketDraft.title } }] },
      Status: { select: { name: "New" } },
      Priority: { select: { name: feedback.priority } },
    },
    children: [
      // Page content blocks
    ],
  });
  
  return {
    externalId: page.id,
    externalUrl: page.url,
  };
}
```

## JSON Export (prd.json format)

For AI dev workflows like Ralph:

```json
{
  "id": "FF-001",
  "title": "User reported bug",
  "acceptanceCriteria": [
    "AI-generated criteria",
    "Based on feedback content"
  ],
  "priority": 1,
  "notes": "Original feedback description"
}
```

### Bulk Export

```typescript
export function exportToPrdJson(feedbackItems: Feedback[]): PrdJson {
  return {
    userStories: feedbackItems.map((item, index) => ({
      id: `FF-${String(index + 1).padStart(3, "0")}`,
      title: item.title,
      acceptanceCriteria: item.aiAnalysis?.acceptanceCriteria || [],
      priority: priorityToNumber(item.priority),
      notes: item.description,
    })),
  };
}
```

## Webhooks

### Configuration
- URL with secret for HMAC signature
- Events: `new_feedback`, `status_changed`, `exported`
- Retry: 3 attempts with exponential backoff

### Payload

```typescript
interface WebhookPayload {
  event: "new_feedback" | "status_changed" | "exported";
  timestamp: number;
  data: {
    feedbackId: string;
    projectId: string;
    // Event-specific data
  };
}
```

## Automation Rules

Trigger automatic exports based on conditions:

```typescript
// Example: All critical bugs → Export to Linear
{
  trigger: "new_feedback",
  conditions: [
    { field: "type", operator: "equals", value: "bug" },
    { field: "priority", operator: "equals", value: "critical" },
  ],
  action: "export_linear",
}
```
